content.description: Go up three bolts through easier terrain before traversing a ledge to a large pod.  Getting past here is the crux.  It is well protected and you can in fact clip two bolts from a stance and essentially be on top rope for the crux move. Good route!
content.protection: 5 bolts and chain anchors with a biner.
content.location: This is the furthest right route located around the corner from Black Lung on the same blueish grey rock.

content.description: Very fun short route.  Great pockets where you want them and great feet when you need them.  A wee bit chossy.  Finishes at the undercling right before the thing gets crazy.  Continue past for a hard/fun looking project.
content.location: Furthest route to the left when looking at the cave.  Use a fixed line to traverse the ledges to get to the first bolt where another fixed line is hanging.

content.description: An excellent stemming challenge up gritty solid limestone.  The crux comes early.  This climb features a tufa, the only one I've ran into in the canyon.  Very airy climb as you are stemming above the void for the majority of the route.
content.protection: 6 bolts and chains with biner anchor
content.location: This climb is on the right side of the cave.  It starts in the smooth looking grey/blue chimney.  This climb veers right of the 12b face (the first two hangers for the 12b are gone for some reason?)
